p: Upon enrolment, the mean alanine aminotransferase (ALT) and mean aspartate aminotransferase (AST) levels of patients with CHIKV were within the normal range (55.13 IU/L and 60.90 IU/L, respectively) while DENV patients had significantly higher mean levels of ALT (113.4 IU/L) and AST (158.7 IU/L) ( Table 2).
